Added support for Liebert DS Unit.

lgpEnvTemperature.name: lgpEnvTemperature
lgpEnvTemperature.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert temperature object identifiers.
lgpEnvTemperature.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Temperature Group.

lgpEnvHumidity.name: lgpEnvHumidity
lgpEnvHumidity.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert humidity object identifiers.
lgpEnvHumidity.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Humidity Group.

lgpEnvState.name: lgpEnvState
lgpEnvState.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental state object identifiers.
lgpEnvState.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental State Group.

lgpEnvConfig.name: lgpEnvConfig
lgpEnvConfig.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental configuration object identifiers.
lgpEnvConfig.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Configuration Group.

lgpEnvControl.name: lgpEnvControl
lgpEnvControl.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental control object identifiers.
lgpEnvControl.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Control Group.

lgpEnvStatistics.name: lgpEnvStatistics
lgpEnvStatistics.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental statistic object identifiers.
lgpEnvStatistics.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Statistics Group.

lgpEnvPoints.name: lgpEnvPoints
lgpEnvPoints.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental point object identifiers.
lgpEnvPoints.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental point Group.

lgpEnvUnits.name: lgpEnvUnits
lgpEnvUnits.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental unit object identifiers.
lgpEnvUnits.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental units Group.

lgpEnvRemoteSensors.name: lgpEnvRemoteSensors
lgpEnvRemoteSensors.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert environmental remote sensor object identifiers.
lgpEnvRemoteSensors.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Remote Sensor Group.

lgpEnvTemperatureWellKnown.name: lgpEnvTemperatureWellKnown
lgpEnvTemperatureWellKnown.description: Liebert well known temperature objects are identified by OIDs that reside in this sub-tree.

lgpEnvTemperatureFahrenheit.name: lgpEnvTemperatureFahrenheit
lgpEnvTemperatureFahrenheit.description: This sub-tree contains OIDs that are used to control and monitor temperature using the Fahrenheit temperature scale.
lgpEnvTemperatureFahrenheit.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Fahrenheit Temperature Group.

lgpEnvTemperatureCelsius.name: lgpEnvTemperatureCelsius
lgpEnvTemperatureCelsius.description: This sub-tree contains OIDs that are used to control and monitor temperature using the Celsius temperature scale.
lgpEnvTemperatureCelsius.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Celsius Temperature Group.

lgpEnvTemperatureControlMode.name: lgpEnvTemperatureControlMode
lgpEnvTemperatureControlMode.description: A reference to a temperature description object. The object referenced should not be accessible, but rather be used to provide a unique description of the temperature object that is used for control.

lgpEnvHumidityWellKnown.name: lgpEnvHumidityWellKnown
lgpEnvHumidityWellKnown.description: Liebert well known humidity objects are defined by OIDs that reside in this sub-tree.

lgpEnvHumidityRelative.name: lgpEnvHumidityRelative
lgpEnvHumidityRelative.description: This sub-tree contains OIDs that are used to control and monitor relative humidity.
lgpEnvHumidityRelative.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Environmental Relative Humidity Group.

lgpEnvStateSystem.name: lgpEnvStateSystem
lgpEnvStateSystem.description: The present state of the system.

lgpEnvStateCooling.name: lgpEnvStateCooling
lgpEnvStateCooling.description: The present state of the cooling subsystem.

lgpEnvStateHeating.name: lgpEnvStateHeating
lgpEnvStateHeating.description: The present state of the heating subsystem.

lgpEnvStateHumidifying.name: lgpEnvStateHumidifying
lgpEnvStateHumidifying.description: The present state of the humidifier subsystem.

lgpEnvStateDehumidifying.name: lgpEnvStateDehumidifying
lgpEnvStateDehumidifying.description: The present state of the dehumidifier subsystem

lgpEnvStateEconoCycle.name: lgpEnvStateEconoCycle
lgpEnvStateEconoCycle.description: The present state of the Econ-o-cycle subsystem.

lgpEnvStateFan.name: lgpEnvStateFan
lgpEnvStateFan.description: The present state of the system fan.

lgpEnvStateGeneralAlarmOutput.name: lgpEnvStateGeneralAlarmOutput
lgpEnvStateGeneralAlarmOutput.description: The present state of the general alarm output. This indicates if an alarm is active in the system.

lgpEnvStateCoolingCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingCapacity
lgpEnvStateCoolingCapacity.description: The percentage of the cooling capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateHeatingCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingCapacity
lgpEnvStateHeatingCapacity.description: The percentage of the heating capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateAudibleAlarm.name: lgpEnvStateAudibleAlarm
lgpEnvStateAudibleAlarm.description: The present state of the audible alarm output.

lgpEnvStateCoolingUnits.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingUnits
lgpEnvStateCoolingUnits.description: This sub-tree contains OIDs that are used to indicate the status of cooling units.

lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit1.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit1
lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit1.description: The present state of cooling unit 1.

lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit2.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit2
lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit2.description: The present state of cooling unit 2.

lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit3.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit3
lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit3.description: The present state of cooling unit 3.

lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit4.name: lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit4
lgpEnvStateCoolingUnit4.description: The present state of cooling unit 4.

lgpEnvStateHeatingUnits.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingUnits
lgpEnvStateHeatingUnits.description: This sub-tree contains OIDs that are used to indicate the status of heating units.

lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit1.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit1
lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit1.description: The present state of heating unit 1.

lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit2.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit2
lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit2.description: The present state of heating unit 2.

lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit3.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit3
lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit3.description: The present state of heating unit 3.

lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit4.name: lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit4
lgpEnvStateHeatingUnit4.description: The present state of heating unit 4.

lgpEnvStateOperatingReason.name: lgpEnvStateOperatingReason
lgpEnvStateOperatingReason.description: The reason for the current operating state of the system.

lgpEnvStateOperatingMode.name: lgpEnvStateOperatingMode
lgpEnvStateOperatingMode.description: The present operating mode of the system.

lgpEnvStateFanCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateFanCapacity
lgpEnvStateFanCapacity.description: The percentage of the fan capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateFreeCoolingCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateFreeCoolingCapacity
lgpEnvStateFreeCoolingCapacity.description: The percentage of the free cooling capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateDehumidifyingCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateDehumidifyingCapacity
lgpEnvStateDehumidifyingCapacity.description: The percentage of the dehumidifying capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateHumidifyingCapacity.name: lgpEnvStateHumidifyingCapacity
lgpEnvStateHumidifyingCapacity.description: The percentage of the humidifying capacity presently in use.

lgpEnvStateFreeCooling.name: lgpEnvStateFreeCooling
lgpEnvStateFreeCooling.description: The present state of the system free cooling process of heat exchange. When 'off', free cooling is not in use. When 'on' free cooling is in use. When 'start', free cooling is preparing to turn on. When 'unavailable', the state information is unavailable.

lgpEnvStateElectricHeater.name: lgpEnvStateElectricHeater
lgpEnvStateElectricHeater.description: The present state of the electric heaters.

lgpEnvStateHotWater.name: lgpEnvStateHotWater
lgpEnvStateHotWater.description: The present state of hot water system.

lgpEnvStateOperatingEfficiency.name: lgpEnvStateOperatingEfficiency
lgpEnvStateOperatingEfficiency.description: The ratio of cooling energy provided to the amount of total energy being used.

lgpEnvComponentStateTable.name: lgpEnvComponentStateTable
lgpEnvComponentStateTable.description: This table contains a list of the units components that have a state associated with them. The table contains zero, one, or more rows, depending upon the number of components associated with the unit. The NMS cannot create or delete rows in the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the units being monitored.

lgpEnvComponentStateEntry.name: lgpEnvComponentStateEntry
lgpEnvComponentStateEntry.description: This entry defines the attributes to be populated in the various columns of the 'lgpEnvComponentStateTable'.

lgpEnvComponentStateIndex.name: lgpEnvComponentStateIndex
lgpEnvComponentStateIndex.description: This is the index indicating the nth element of the table.

lgpEnvComponentStateDescr.name: lgpEnvComponentStateDescr
lgpEnvComponentStateDescr.description: A reference to a component description object. The object referenced should not be accessible, but rather be used to provide a unique description of the component being described in the row of the table.

lgpEnvComponentState.name: lgpEnvComponentState
lgpEnvComponentState.description: not-specified The state of the component is unknown. on The component is on. off The component is off.

lgpEnvValveTable.name: lgpEnvValveTable
lgpEnvValveTable.description: This table contains a list of the unit valves that have information associated with them. The table contains zero, one, or more rows, depending upon the number of valves associated with the unit. The NMS cannot create or delete rows in the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the units being monitored.

lgpEnvValveEntry.name: lgpEnvValveEntry
lgpEnvValveEntry.description: This entry defines the attributes to be populated in the various columns of the 'lgpEnvValveTable'.

lgpEnvValveIndex.name: lgpEnvValveIndex
lgpEnvValveIndex.description: This is the index indicating the nth element of the table.

lgpEnvValveDescr.name: lgpEnvValveDescr
lgpEnvValveDescr.description: A reference to a valve description object. The object referenced should not be accessible, but rather be used to provide a unique description of the valve being described in the row of the table.

lgpEnvValveState.name: lgpEnvValveState
lgpEnvValveState.description: not-specified The state of the component is unknown. open The valve is open. off The valve is closed.

lgpEnvValvePositionTenths.name: lgpEnvValvePositionTenths
lgpEnvValvePositionTenths.description: This gives a value describing the position of the valve.

lgpEnvConfigReheatLockout.name: lgpEnvConfigReheatLockout
lgpEnvConfigReheatLockout.description: If locked-out the reheats will not operate even if controller calls for its operation.

lgpEnvConfigHumLockout.name: lgpEnvConfigHumLockout
lgpEnvConfigHumLockout.description: If locked-out the humidifier will not operate even if controller calls for its operation.

lgpEnvConfigRestartDelay.name: lgpEnvConfigRestartDelay
lgpEnvConfigRestartDelay.description: When utility power is disrupted, this is the delay interval to wait before restarting the system after the utility power is restored. A Restart Delay of zero denotes a manual restart, the unit will NOT automatically restart.

lgpEnvConfigRemoteShutdown.name: lgpEnvConfigRemoteShutdown
lgpEnvConfigRemoteShutdown.description: When in the disabled state, the remote shutdown feature should be locked out. The enabled state is self-describing.

lgpEnvConfigCoolingServiceInterval.name: lgpEnvConfigCoolingServiceInterval
lgpEnvConfigCoolingServiceInterval.description: The amount of time, in hours, between scheduled maintenance of the cooling system. When the cooling service timer reaches this value an lgpConditionServiceCooling will be activated. Once service has been completed the cooling service timer should be reset to 0.

lgpEnvConfigHumidifierServiceInterval.name: lgpEnvConfigHumidifierServiceInterval
lgpEnvConfigHumidifierServiceInterval.description: The amount of time, in hours, between scheduled maintenance of the humidifier. When the humidifier service timer reaches this value an lgpConditionServiceHumidifier will be activated. Once service has been completed humidifier service timer should be reset to 0.

lgpEnvConfigFilterServiceInterval.name: lgpEnvConfigFilterServiceInterval
lgpEnvConfigFilterServiceInterval.description: The amount of time, in hours, between scheduled maintenance of the system filter. When the filter service timer reaches this value an lgpConditionChangeFilter will be activated. Once service has been completed the filter service timer should be reset to 0.

lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegC.name: lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegC
lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegC.description: The allowable deviation above and below the temperature set point used to create a no control region, a dead-band, where heating and cooling control are disabled. This dead-band is applied only when the system's sleep mode function is in operation.

lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegF.name: lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegF
lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRangeDegF.description: The allowable deviation above and below the temperature set point used to create a no control region, a dead-band, where heating and cooling control are disabled. This dead-band is applied only when the system's sleep mode function is in operation.

lgpEnvConfigTemperatureIntegTime.name: lgpEnvConfigTemperatureIntegTime
lgpEnvConfigTemperatureIntegTime.description: The value used as the integration factor in the proportional integral derivative (PID) temperature calculation.

lgpEnvConfigLocalTemperatureUnit.name: lgpEnvConfigLocalTemperatureUnit
lgpEnvConfigLocalTemperatureUnit.description: The local temperature unit of the system.

lgpEnvConfigSleepMode.name: lgpEnvConfigSleepMode
lgpEnvConfigSleepMode.description: The configured mode of the device's sleep function. If 'enabled', the device will sleep, or not operate, for each 'lgpEnvSleepDay' that is enabled and also during the periods defined in the 'lgpEnvSleepTimeTable' each day. If 'disabled', the device will operate continually and not sleep at all. If 'auto', the device will sleep, or not operate, for each 'lgpEnvSleepDay' that is enabled and also during the periods defined in the 'lgpEnvSleepTimeTable' each day unless the environmental conditions fall outside the desired operation ranges.

lgpEnvConfigHumidityIntegTime.name: lgpEnvConfigHumidityIntegTime
lgpEnvConfigHumidityIntegTime.description: The value used as the integration factor in the proportional integral derivative (PID) humidity calculation.

lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegF.name: lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegF
lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegF.description: The minimum temperature differential between the control temperature measurement and the coolant required to utilize free-cooling.

lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegC.name: lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegC
lgpEnvConfigFreecoolingDeltaDegC.description: The minimum temperature differential between the control temperature measurement and the coolant required to utilize free-cooling.

lgpEnvConfigSupplyTempLowLimit.name: lgpEnvConfigSupplyTempLowLimit
lgpEnvConfigSupplyTempLowLimit.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable the supply air low temperature limit.

lgpEnvConfigSensorEventsStandard.name: lgpEnvConfigSensorEventsStandard
lgpEnvConfigSensorEventsStandard.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable the standard sensor events.

lgpEnvConfigSensorEvents1.name: lgpEnvConfigSensorEvents1
lgpEnvConfigSensorEvents1.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable sensor 1 events.

lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRange.name: lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRange
lgpEnvConfigSleepModeDeadbandRange.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable the use of the sleep interval dead-band range in the sleep mode temperature calculations and control algorithm.

lgpEnvConfigAutoConfiguration.name: lgpEnvConfigAutoConfiguration
lgpEnvConfigAutoConfiguration.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable the auto configuration feature. This feature configures temperature and humidity control parameters.

lgpEnvConfigDeltaGlycolType.name: lgpEnvConfigDeltaGlycolType
lgpEnvConfigDeltaGlycolType.description: The system configuration parameter that specifies how the system will determine if there is enough capacity to initiate free cooling. If 'disabled', the system will use the valve temperature to initiate free cooling. If 'contact', a input to the system will initiate free cooling. If 'valve', the system compares the room and glycol temperature differential with the valve temperature to initiate free cooling. If the temperature differential is greater than or equal to the valve temperature, free cooling will be initiated.

lgpEnvConfigChillWaterControl.name: lgpEnvConfigChillWaterControl
lgpEnvConfigChillWaterControl.description: The system configuration parameter to enable or disable the minimum chill water temperature control.

lgpEnvConfigInfaredFlushRate.name: lgpEnvConfigInfaredFlushRate
lgpEnvConfigInfaredFlushRate.description: The Infrared humidifier pan overfill rate. This parameter configures the amount of water that flows into the humidifier pan when the 'humidifier is in operation.

lgpEnvConfigHumidityControl.name: lgpEnvConfigHumidityControl
lgpEnvConfigHumidityControl.description: The present configured state of the automatic humidity compensation algorithm.

lgpEnvConfigCompressorLockout.name: lgpEnvConfigCompressorLockout
lgpEnvConfigCompressorLockout.description: The system as locked out the compressor(s). If locked-out, the compressor(s) will not operate even if the controller calls for their operation.

lgpEnvConfigReheatAndHumidifierLockout.name: lgpEnvConfigReheatAndHumidifierLockout
lgpEnvConfigReheatAndHumidifierLockout.description: The system as locked out the compressor(s). If locked-out, the electrical reheats and humidifier will not operate even if the controller calls for their operation.

lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable.name: lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable
lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable.description: A list of environmental operational time ranges for a given environmental unit. The entries in this table may be duplicated from values in the 'lgpEnvStatistics' group. This table contains zero, one, or many rows, depending upon the number of 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint' and 'lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID' available in the table. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpEnvOperationalTimeEntry.name: lgpEnvOperationalTimeEntry
lgpEnvOperationalTimeEntry.reference: The 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint' in this table corresponds to what the operation time applies to.
lgpEnvOperationalTimeEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvOperationTimeIndex.name: lgpEnvOperationTimeIndex
lgpEnvOperationTimeIndex.description: This is the index indicating the nth element of the table.

lgpEnvOperationTimePoint.name: lgpEnvOperationTimePoint
lgpEnvOperationTimePoint.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpEnvWellKnownPoints' and correspond to the entry in the table 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.
lgpEnvOperationTimePoint.description: An OID representing a well known operation point. These object identifiers can indicate a point, location, or mode of an operation for which a measurement is recorded. The OID's name usually implies a location of the measurement point such as 'fan', 'compressor', etc.

lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID.name: lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID
lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID.description: This is a sub identifier for the 'lgpEnvOperationPoint'. It indicates the instance number of the well known operation point. For example, a system could have two fans installed. This variable would identify fan 1 with a lgpEnvOperationSubID equal to 1 and fan 2 with a lgpEnvOperationSubID equal to 2.

lgpEnvOperationTimeUnit.name: lgpEnvOperationTimeUnit
lgpEnvOperationTimeUnit.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpEnvWellKnownUnits' and correspond to the entry in the table lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable.
lgpEnvOperationTimeUnit.description: An OID representing a well known operation time unit type. These object identifiers indicate the units of the operation time. The OID's name usually implies a measurement type such as 'lgpEnvHours', etc.

lgpEnvOperationTimeValue.name: lgpEnvOperationTimeValue
lgpEnvOperationTimeValue.description: The actual operation time value of the 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint'. If multiple operation times are available for a 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint' the 'lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID' will differentiate between them.

lgpEnvOperationTimeHighWarning.name: lgpEnvOperationTimeHighWarning
lgpEnvOperationTimeHighWarning.description: The high warning time of the operation designated by the 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint'. If operation times are available at a single 'lgpEnvOperationTimePoint' the 'lgpEnvOperationTimeSubID' will differentiate between them.

lgpEnvConfigTempControlAlgorithm.name: lgpEnvConfigTempControlAlgorithm
lgpEnvConfigTempControlAlgorithm.description: Selects the algorithm for controlling temperature.

lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode.name: lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode
lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode.description: Changes the function of the fan speed output. If auto, then the fan speed is modulated. If manual, the fan speed output follows lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedCapacity.

lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedCapacity.name: lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedCapacity
lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedCapacity.description: Sets the fan speed output if lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode is set to 'manual'. Typical values range from 0 to 100% (actual valid ranges may differ from unit to unit).

lgpEnvConfigBmsResetTimer.name: lgpEnvConfigBmsResetTimer
lgpEnvConfigBmsResetTimer.description: The current count-down time for a BMS to continue controlling the fan speed. If this value reaches 0, then the condition lgpConditionBmsResetTimerExpired will be generated. If a BMS wants to continue controlling the fan speed, it must reset this timer. Typical values range from 0 to 120 minutes (actual valid ranges may differ from unit to unit).

lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegC.name: lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegC
lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegC.description: If any of the enclosure temperature sensors (lgpEnvEnclosureTemperatureSensors) are outside the average reading by this amount, that sensor's readings will not be used.

lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegF.name: lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegF
lgpEnvConfigDisableSensorOffsetDegF.description: If any of the enclosure temperature sensors (lgpEnvEnclosureTemperatureSensors) are outside the average reading by this amount, that sensor's readings will not be used.

lgpEnvConfigCabinetSensorAlarms.name: lgpEnvConfigCabinetSensorAlarms
lgpEnvConfigCabinetSensorAlarms.description: Enable or Disable Cabinet Sensor Alarms.

lgpEnvConfigAirTemperatureControlSensor.name: lgpEnvConfigAirTemperatureControlSensor
lgpEnvConfigAirTemperatureControlSensor.description: Sensor from which air temperature measurements will be used for cooling and heating control.

lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedControlSensor.name: lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedControlSensor
lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedControlSensor.description: Sensor from which air temperature measurements will be used for fan speed control.

lgpEnvConfigMinFanSpeed.name: lgpEnvConfigMinFanSpeed
lgpEnvConfigMinFanSpeed.description: Sets the minimum fan speed output if lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode is set to 'Auto'.

lgpEnvConfigMaxFanSpeed.name: lgpEnvConfigMaxFanSpeed
lgpEnvConfigMaxFanSpeed.description: Sets the maximum fan speed output if lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedMode is set to 'Auto'.

lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegC.name: lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegC
lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegC.description: Temperature control band above the temperature set point calculated for proportional fan speed control. If measured air temperature is within this band, fan speed operations are proportionally controlled.

lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegF.name: lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegF
lgpEnvConfigFanSpeedPropBandDegF.description: Temperature control band above the temperature set point calculated for proportional fan speed control. If measured air temperature is within this band, fan speed operations are proportionally controlled.

lgpEnvControlShutdownAfterDelay.name: lgpEnvControlShutdownAfterDelay
lgpEnvControlShutdownAfterDelay.description: Setting this object will shutdown (i.e., turn off) the system after the indicated number of seconds. Setting this object to 0 will cause the shutdown to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown. If the system is already in the desired state at the time the countdown reaches 0, then nothing will happen. When read, lgpEnvControlShutdownAfterDelay will return the number of seconds remaining until shutdown, or -1 if no shutdown countdown is in effect. On some systems, if the agent is restarted while a shutdown countdown is in effect, the countdown may be aborted. Sets to this object override any lgpEnvControlShutdownAfterDelay already in effect.

lgpEnvControlStartupAfterDelay.name: lgpEnvControlStartupAfterDelay
lgpEnvControlStartupAfterDelay.description: Setting this object will start the system after the indicated number of seconds. Setting this object to 0 will cause the startup to occur immediately. Setting this object to -1 will abort the countdown. If the system is already on at the time the countdown reaches 0, then nothing will happen. Sets to this object override the effect of any lgpEnvControlStartupAfterDelay countdown in progress. When read, lgpEnvControlStartupAfterDelay will return the number of seconds until startup, or -1 if no startup countdown is in effect. On some systems, if the agent is restarted while a startup countdown is in effect, the countdown is aborted.

lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeTable.name: lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeTable
lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeTable.description: A sleep time interval table containing a list of the start and stop times to be used to take a device online or offline. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeEntry.name: lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeEntry
lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvSleepTimeIndex.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeIndex
lgpEnvSleepTimeIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvSleepTimeSubID.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeSubID
lgpEnvSleepTimeSubID.description: This is a sub identifier for each 'lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeEntry'. It indicates the instance number of the 'lgpEnvSleepIntervalTimeEntry'. For example, a system could have two sleep intervals and the first interval's sub ID would be 1 and the second interval's sub ID would be 2.

lgpEnvSleepTimeStartHour.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeStartHour
lgpEnvSleepTimeStartHour.description: This is the hours digit of the time when the system will be put online.

lgpEnvSleepTimeStartMinute.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeStartMinute
lgpEnvSleepTimeStartMinute.description: This is the minutes digit of the time when the system will be put online.

lgpEnvSleepTimeStopHour.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeStopHour
lgpEnvSleepTimeStopHour.description: This is the hours digit containing the time when the system will be taken offline.

lgpEnvSleepTimeStopMinute.name: lgpEnvSleepTimeStopMinute
lgpEnvSleepTimeStopMinute.description: This is the minutes digit containing the time when the system will be taken offline.

lgpEnvSleepDayTable.name: lgpEnvSleepDayTable
lgpEnvSleepDayTable.description: A sleep table containing a list of the days of the week the system will be offline. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpEnvSleepDayEntry.name: lgpEnvSleepDayEntry
lgpEnvSleepDayEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpEnvSleepDayTable'.

lgpEnvSleepDayIndex.name: lgpEnvSleepDayIndex
lgpEnvSleepDayIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpEnvSleepDayTable'.

lgpEnvSleepDay.name: lgpEnvSleepDay
lgpEnvSleepDay.description: This is a sub identifier for the day of the week within 'lgpEnvSleepDayTable'.

lgpEnvSleepAllDayEnabled.name: lgpEnvSleepAllDayEnabled
lgpEnvSleepAllDayEnabled.description: The all day sleep functionality has been enabled for the corresponding 'lgpEnvSleepDay' in the 'lgpEnvSleepDayTable'.

lgpEnvStatisticsComp1RunHr.name: lgpEnvStatisticsComp1RunHr
lgpEnvStatisticsComp1RunHr.description: Accumulated run hours of compressor 1. This value may be duplicated in the 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvStatisticsComp2RunHr.name: lgpEnvStatisticsComp2RunHr
lgpEnvStatisticsComp2RunHr.description: Accumulated run hours of compressor 2. This value may be duplicated in the 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvStatisticsFanRunHr.name: lgpEnvStatisticsFanRunHr
lgpEnvStatisticsFanRunHr.description: Accumulated run hours of the main fan. This value may be duplicated in the 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.

lgpEnvStatisticsHumRunHr.name: lgpEnvStatisticsHumRunHr
lgpEnvStatisticsHumRunHr.description: Accumulated run hours of the humidifier. This value may be duplicated in the 'lgpEnvOperationalTimeTable'.
